{"id":"project-LICHEN-lsri","title":"ConfigResource.set_config has no authorization check","description":"File: python/src/lichen/coap/resources.py:166-176

render_put allows any CoAP client to modify node configuration:
```python
async def render_put(self, request: Message) -> Message:
    if not request.payload:
        return Message(code=BAD_REQUEST)
    try:
        updates = cbor2.loads(request.payload)
    except Exception:
        return Message(code=BAD_REQUEST)
    if not isinstance(updates, dict):
        return Message(code=BAD_REQUEST)
    self.node_info.set_config(updates)
    return Message(code=CHANGED)
```

There is no authentication or authorization check. Any network attacker can reconfigure the node, potentially:
1. Disabling security features
2. Changing routing parameters
3. Redirecting traffic

This violates spec section 8 security requirements.

